# Tool listing bullet DNA (permanent — locked)

All tool catalog listing (`free-tools`, `pro-tools`, category pages, industry hubs, search results) must use the **bullet list** style as the default listing DNA.

## Grid specification (locked)

```
grid grid-cols-1 gap-x-6 gap-y-[10px] sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3
```

Breakpoints:
- **Mobile** (default): 1 column
- **Small** (`sm`): 2 columns
- **Large** (`lg`): 3 columns — maximum width

## Required components

- **`ToolAlphaList`** (`src/components/tools/ToolAlphaList.tsx`) — single bullet-list component for tool lists
- Use `ToolAlphaList` via `ToolListItems` inner component for the bullet grid

## Rules

- Every tool listing section must display tools in **3-column grid** (`lg:grid-cols-3`) as the maximum width.
- Never use single-column vertical stacks for tool lists.
- Never use 2-column-only grids (`md:grid-cols-2` without `lg:grid-cols-3`).
- The A-Z index sections already use `lg:grid-cols-3` — keep them in sync.
- `ToolAlphaList` is the single source of truth for bullet list grid; change it once, all listings update.

## Visual style

- Each tool: bullet (`&bull;`) + link with `text-blue-700 hover:text-blue-800 hover:underline truncate`
- No card backgrounds, no borders, no arrow icons in listing sections
- The category detail panel in `CategoryCatalogView` may use card-style items, but the main catalog listing goes through `ToolAlphaList`

